[normal]ll my evidence would be drawn from large-scale statistical studies of transactions, and that is where you c
[normal]an get really fine detail. It
[normal] is not just a question of two semi
[normal]-
[normal]detached houses in the same road being rather similar, but you can identify statistically the implic
[normal]it price of each attribute. E
[normal]very property is different
[normal],
[normal] but it is compose
[normal]d of a bundle of attributes. If 
[normal]you have got a large sample of transactions
[normal]—a 
[normal]colleague at the LSE has just been analysing 1
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]million house transactions to identify the price that is put on green belt land
[normal]—
[normal]you can get very accurate
[normal] statistical evidence, but I would never trust a valuer to give me an accurate answer.
