[normal]Professor Cheshire[bold]: If you want to bring forward development. It was a conditional statement. It depends on what your policy objectives are. Broadly, there are reasons for having comparable tax treatment for all productive assets. Land is a productive asset. You might argue that there are social dimensions to land use, but there are certainly environmental issues associated with land use which suggest you should have a particular tax treatment to favour certain categories. In general, the lower the prices of agricultural land
[normal],
[normal] the more variety of ownership and the more environmental benefits you will get.
