[normal]Professor Cheshire[bold]: I do not have detailed knowledge of the Scottish situation, but across most of England
[normal],
[normal] housing is so valuable because of the restriction on supply that it is crowding out other uses. If you look at the price of land zoned for industry relative to land zoned for housing, there is a big discontinuity there. There is a similar discontinuity at the boundary between land zoned for offices compared with land zoned for housing. Certainly, in most English cities
[normal],
